==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penitential
<hw>Pen`i*ten"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧nitentiel</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to
penitence, or to penance; expressing penitence; of the nature of
penance; <as>as, the <ex>penitential</ex> book; <ex>penitential</ex>
tears.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Penitential</xex> stripes.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Guilt that all the <qex>penitential</qex> fires of hereafter can
not cleanse.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penitential</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Penitential
<hw>Pen`i*ten"tial</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>A
book formerly used by priests hearing confessions, containing rules for
the imposition of penances; -- called also <altname>penitential
book</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penitentially</ent>⟦br⟧
